OL,3,CTeacher spent #28,000 in loans from
OL,4,Cpupils' parents on flights and visa
OL,6,FThe parents said Mrs Pletnick made
OL,7,F"false promises" and she did not repay
OL,8,Fany of the #22,740 she owed ` and they
OL,9,Fadded that lending the money has "had
OL,10,Fdevastating financial consequences"
OL,11,Ffor them, the tribunal was told.
OL,13,FAnother parent of a pupil lent Mrs
OL,14,FPletnick #1,500 during her employment
OL,15,Fat the school after she said she had
OL,16,Fbeen unwell and needed money to have
OL,17,Fan operation privately ` and the loan
OL,18,Fwas not repaid, the panel heard.
